provisioning service that they have created. Azure IoT Central has a DPS under the hood, and to connect from a number of SDKs you need to call the DPS using IoT Central connection details to get back the IoT Hub to connect to.

It would be great to somehow expand on this documentation, either here or in the IoT Central docs to show how to use the DPS inside IoT Central to provision a device and connect. This comes as customer feedback from a lecturer who is using the C SDK via an IoT Hub template in Mbed OS and wants to connect to IoT Central.
